column1: Who will win the election for Arizona's 4th Congressional District in 2022?
column5: ['The Democratic Party candidate', 'The Republican Party candidate', 'Someone else']

column6: The prediction markets, poll aggregates, and forecasts are unanimous: this one is blue.

538 is very bullish on this race, favoring Stanton (D) over Cooper (R) 92 times out of 100. The professional forecasters (Cook, et al) are a little more conservative in their estimates, which range anywhere from "lean" to "likely" Democrat. I found a PBS news article portraying this race as the "most competitive in Arizona." It cited 538, and I wondered if we were looking at the same site. Given, this article was published a couple weeks ago, but Stanton had an even greater probability of winning on the date in question, with a projected popular vote margin of 10 points. I'll keep my eyes on this one, but I doubt it's going to suddenly get competitive down the stretch.
I thought this district was district 8 area, district 4 is in the heart of Phoenix, and it has been slowing turning blue for some time.

The 4th district is outside of major cities that have been turning purple/blue. The major rural areas are more independent and are seeing the brunt of southern border. Likely a republican will continue to hold the seat.
The Cook Political Report, Split Ticket, and CNalysis have all just changed their AZ-04 ratings from "Lean D" to "Likely D":
On Aug 29, Split Ticket changed their AZ-04 rating from "Leans D" to "Likely D": https://split-ticket.org/2022/08/29/house-temperature-check/

Hedging a lot towards general consensus on a lot of these election questions. I consistently rate GOP as more likely than the 538/predictit/GJO conensus, but I don't want to overrate it too much or else I could get totally blown out since all of these are correlated with each other.
Don't believe in splitting forecast in a two horse race.
current rep is a democrat; limited polling data seems to believe likely go democrat
+1 Dem lean district in a +6 GOP year = +5 GOP baseline

Arizona's 4th Congessional District has a 2021 Cook Political Report rating of R+22... although it's unclear to me if the district boundaries have changed due to redistricting prior to the 2022 election.
